  "steps": [
    {
      "order": 1,
      "instruction": "Preheat the oven to 475 degrees F. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper."
    },
    {
      "order": 2,
      "instruction": "To a blender, add the olive oil, pomegranate molasses, coconut rum (if using), habanero chilies, ginger, garlic, green onions, cilantro, thyme, all-spice, cinnamon salt and pepper. Blend until smooth. Add in more olive oil if the sauce seems a little too thick."
    },
    {
      "order": 3,
      "instruction": "Now grab the oranges, grapefruit and limes and very thinly slice them. Lay the slices along with the pineapple slices on the prepared baking sheet. Place the chicken pieces over the citrus. Brush each chicken piece with the sauce."
    },
    {
      "order": 4,
      "instruction": "Roast for 25-30 minutes or until the chicken is cooked throughout. I brushed my chicken with the remaining sauce half way through roasting. Serve the chicken with the roasted citrus slices."
    }
  ]
